Free Spoken Digit Dataset Classifier - Execution Steps
=====================================================

1. Prerequisites
---------------
- Ensure Python 3.8 or higher is installed.
- Use a virtual environment (recommended) to isolate dependencies.

2. Clone the Repository
-----------------------
git clone https://username:access_token@your-repository-url.git
cd LLM_Coding_Challenge.git

3. Create and Activate Virtual Environment
------------------------------------------
# On macOS/Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# On Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

4. Install Required Libraries
-----------------------------
pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Configure Environment Variables
---------------------------------
Create a `.env` file in the root directory with the following content:

SAMPLE_RATE=8000
N_MFCC=13
MAX_LEN=8000
MODEL_PATH="model/random_forest.pkl"

6. Run the Main Program
-----------------------
python main.py


7. Notes
--------
- The program downloads the Free Spoken Digit Dataset automatically.
- For microphone input, ensure your mic is set up and permissions granted.
- To retrain or evaluate with different parameters, adjust `.env` values accordingly.

Enjoy your project!
